name: Secret Bao
address: 1201 Anacapa St, Santa Barbara, CA 93101, USA
description_short: Santa Barbara, California is known for its stunning coastline, scenic vineyards, and fantastic food. One local eatery that has gained national attention is Secret Bao, a small Chinese-American fusion restaurant that was featured on the popular TV show Diners, Drive-Ins, and Dives with Guy Fieri.
description_long: Santa Barbara, California is known for its stunning coastline, scenic vineyards, and fantastic food. One local eatery that has gained national attention is Secret Bao, a small Chinese-American fusion restaurant that was featured on the popular TV show Diners, Drive-Ins, and Dives with Guy Fieri.Located on the busy thoroughfare of State Street, Secret Bao is a modest-looking establishment that might be easy to miss if you’re not looking for it. But once you step inside, you’ll be greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere, with friendly staff and mouth-watering aromas wafting from the kitchen.The star of Secret Bao's menu is, unsurprisingly, their bao buns. These steamed buns filled with various meats and vegetables are a popular street food in China, but Secret Bao takes them to the next level by infusing them with bold flavors and creative ingredients.One of the restaurant's most famous bao buns is the Korean Fried Chicken Bao, which features tender pieces of fried chicken coated in a spicy, tangy sauce and topped with slaw and pickled veggies. The pork belly bao is another crowd-pleaser, with succulent pork belly, cucumber, scallions, and hoisin sauce. Vegetarians can also enjoy the tofu bao, filled with crispy tofu, avocado, and a savory soy sauce.But Secret Bao's menu goes beyond bao buns. They also serve delicious dumplings, noodles, and rice bowls. The pan-fried pork dumplings are crispy and packed with juicy pork filling, while the Dan Dan Noodles are a spicy, savory delight.Another must-try dish is the Hainanese Chicken Rice Bowl, a traditional Singaporean dish made with poached chicken served over rice cooked in chicken broth and topped with ginger and scallions. It's a simple dish, but one that's bursting with flavor.Guy Fieri visited Secret Bao in 2019, and the restaurant's popularity skyrocketed after the episode aired. But despite the national attention, Secret Bao has stayed true to its roots, serving up delicious food in a relaxed, casual setting.The prices at Secret Bao are reasonable, with most dishes costing around $10-12. You can also order online for pickup or delivery, making it easy to enjoy their food from the comfort of your own home.One thing to note is that Secret Bao is quite popular, and the small space can fill up quickly during peak hours. But if you're willing to wait, you'll be rewarded with some of the best bao buns and Chinese-American fusion cuisine in Santa Barbara.In conclusion, Secret Bao is a hidden gem in Santa Barbara that's definitely worth seeking out. Whether you're a fan of bao buns or just love delicious, inventive food, Secret Bao is sure to satisfy your taste buds. Thanks to their appearance on Diners, Drive-Ins, and Dives, Secret Bao has gained national recognition, but locals have known about this spot for a while. So next time you're in Santa Barbara, make sure to stop by Secret Bao and treat yourself to some unforgettable Chinese-American fusion cuisine.

name: What's Zaap? Thai Food
address: 9575 W Tropicana Ave #1 Las Vegas, NV 89147, USA
description_short: Welcome to our Thai restaurant, where we strive to offer our guests an authentic taste of Thailand right here in Nevada. Our menu is inspired by traditional Thai dishes, but we also like to put our own unique spin on things.
description_long: Welcome to our Thai restaurant, where we strive to offer our guests an authentic taste of Thailand right here in Nevada. Our menu is inspired by traditional Thai dishes, but we also like to put our own unique spin on things.One dish that we're particularly proud of is our Pad Kee Mao, also known as Drunken Noodles. This spicy stir-fry dish features wide rice noodles, fresh vegetables, and your choice of protein, all tossed in a flavorful sauce made with chili peppers, garlic, and basil. It's a favorite among our regulars, and we think you'll love it too.Another must-try dish on our menu is our Khao Soi. This Northern Thai specialty is a rich and creamy curry made with coconut milk and spices, served over crispy egg noodles and topped with fresh herbs and lime. It's a comforting and satisfying dish that's perfect for a chilly day.If you're in the mood for something lighter, we also offer a variety of salads and soups. Our Som Tum salad is a refreshing mix of shredded green papaya, carrots, and peanuts, dressed in a tangy and spicy dressing. And our Tom Kha soup is a fragrant and creamy soup made with coconut milk, lemongrass, and your choice of protein.At our restaurant, we believe that using fresh and high-quality ingredients is the key to great food. That's why we source our produce and meats locally whenever possible, and we make our sauces and curries from scratch.We also take pride in our friendly and welcoming atmosphere. Whether you're dining with family or catching up with friends, our restaurant is the perfect place to relax and enjoy a delicious meal.Our menu features a wide variety of dishes, from classic favorites like Pad Thai and Green Curry to lesser-known specialties like Moo Ping and Larb Gai. Each dish is crafted with care using authentic Thai ingredients and cooking techniques. We also offer vegetarian and vegan options for those with dietary restrictions.One dish that our customers can't get enough of is our Tom Yum soup. This spicy and sour soup is a staple of Thai cuisine and is made with shrimp, lemongrass, lime juice, and chili peppers. It's the perfect dish to warm you up on a chilly day or to help clear out sinuses when you're feeling under the weather.Our restaurant's atmosphere is designed to transport you to Thailand. From the colorful decor to the traditional Thai music playing in the background, we want you to feel as if you're on a culinary adventure in Southeast Asia.We understand the importance of quality ingredients, which is why we source our produce and meats locally whenever possible. This not only ensures that our dishes are fresh but also supports our local community.If you're looking to try something new or craving a taste of home, we invite you to visit our restaurant. Our friendly staff and delicious cuisine are sure to make your dining experience one to remember.In summary, our restaurant offers a wide variety of authentic Thai dishes, including vegetarian and vegan options. Our Tom Yum soup is a customer favorite, and we pride ourselves on using locally sourced ingredients whenever possible. Our restaurant's ambiance is designed to transport you to Thailand, and our friendly staff is dedicated to providing exceptional service. Come dine with us and experience the flavors of Thailand for yourself.

name: NoButcher
address: 3565 S Rainbow Blvd Suite 110, Las Vegas, NV 89103, USA
description_short: If you're looking for a unique vegan restaurant experience, then you need to check out NoButcher in Las Vegas. Located in the heart of the city, NoButcher is a vegan eatery that specializes in plant-based proteins. At NoButcher, all of the proteins are made from plant-based ingredients, and they are all prepared in a way that mimics the taste and texture of traditional meats.They offer a variety of different proteins, such as beef, chicken, pork, and even fish. All of the proteins are made with non-GMO soy and plant-based ingredients, so you can enjoy a delicious meal without the guilt. In addition to their proteins, NoButcher also offers a selection of vegan sides, such as roasted vegetables and potato wedges. They also have a variety of salads, soups, sandwiches, and wraps. All of their dishes are made with fresh, organic ingredients, so you can be sure that you're getting the best quality food. NoButcher also offers a selection of vegan desserts, such as cakes, pies, and ice cream.They also have a full bar, so you can enjoy a vegan cocktail or beer with your meal. "Unleashing the Flavor of Vegan Cuisine at NoButcher in Las Vegas" As a foodie, I am always on the lookout for new and exciting dining experiences, and my recent visit to NoButcher in Las Vegas was truly unforgettable. This vegan restaurant is breaking the mold, offering an unparalleled culinary experience that is not only delicious but also healthy and sustainable. From the moment I walked into the restaurant, I was struck by the warm and inviting atmosphere.The decor is modern and stylish, with an open kitchen concept that allows diners to watch the chefs in action. The menu features a variety of vegan dishes, all of which are carefully crafted using only the freshest, locally sourced ingredients. But let's get to the most important part, the food. I had the chance to try a variety of dishes, and I was blown away by the incredible flavors and textures that were on offer. The BBQ Jackfruit Sandwich was a standout dish, with the slow-cooked jackfruit taking on the flavor and texture of pulled pork. The tangy BBQ sauce and crispy slaw added a delicious crunch to the dish, making it a must-try for any vegan foodie. Another dish that I highly recommend is the Tofu Scramble. This dish is a perfect example of how NoButcher is reimagining traditional meat-based dishes and making them vegan-friendly.The tofu was scrambled to perfection, and the addition of vegetables like bell peppers, onions, and mushrooms added depth to the dish. For dessert, the Chia Pudding was a refreshing and satisfying end to the meal. The creamy pudding was flavored with coconut and topped with fresh fruit and granola, making it a perfect balance of sweet and crunchy. One thing that really sets NoButcher apart is their commitment to using sustainable and eco-friendly practices. They use only biodegradable containers and utensils, and they source their ingredients from local and organic suppliers whenever possible.This focus on sustainability not only benefits the environment, but it also adds a level of quality to the food that is hard to beat. In conclusion, NoButcher is a must-visit destination for anyone visiting Las Vegas who loves delicious food and wants to try something new. Their commitment to vegan cuisine and sustainable practices make this place a true standout in the city's dining scene. Whether you're a vegan or just looking to try something new, NoButcher is the place to be. So, the next time you're in Las Vegas, make sure to stop by NoButcher and taste the magic for yourself. You won't be disappointed!

address: 8125 W Sahara Ave #170, Las Vegas, NV 89117, USA
description_short: If you’re looking for an exciting pizza experience, then you should definitely consider visiting Marsigliano’s Pizzeria & More in Las Vegas. Having just opened its doors in 2020, Marsigliano’s has quickly become a popular spot with locals and tourists alike. Marsigliano’s offers a variety of traditional Italian pizzas, as well as some unique variations. The menu includes a selection of classic pies, such as Margherita and Pepperoni, as well as some more contemporary options, like the Prosciutto Arugula and the Shrimp Puttanesca.Every pizza is made with fresh, made-from-scratch ingredients, and the dough is hand-tossed and cooked to perfection in a wood-fired oven. In addition to their amazing pizzas, Marsigliano’s also offers delicious appetizers, salads, and desserts. The appetizers include classic Italian favorites, such as calamari, bruschetta, and mozzarella sticks. The salads are fresh and flavorful, with options like Caesar, Greek, and Caprese. For dessert, you can enjoy a classic cannoli or the house-specialty tiramisu. "Discovering the Best Pizza in Las Vegas: A Foodie's Journey to Marsigliano's Pizzeria & More" As a food lover, I was excited to embark on a culinary journey to Las Vegas and discover some of the best dining experiences the city has to offer. During my travels, I stumbled upon Marsigliano's Pizzeria & More, and I was blown away by the incredible pizza I tried there.From the moment I walked into the restaurant, I was greeted by the warm and inviting atmosphere. The decor is simple and classic, with a focus on the authentic Italian flavors that are at the heart of every dish. The menu features a variety of traditional and specialty pizzas, as well as other Italian favorites like pasta and salads. But let's get to the most important part, the pizza. I had the chance to try the Margherita pizza, and I have to say, it was the best pizza I have ever had. The crust was perfectly thin and crispy, while the tomato sauce was full of flavor and had just the right amount of acidity. The mozzarella cheese was melted to perfection, and the basil added a fresh, herby note to the dish. One of the things that really sets Marsigliano's apart is their use of high-quality ingredients.They source only the freshest and finest ingredients, including imported Italian cheeses, sauces, and toppings. This attention to detail is evident in every bite of their pizza. In addition to their incredible pizza, I also had the chance to try the spaghetti carbonara, which was just as impressive. The pasta was cooked al dente, and the carbonara sauce was rich, creamy, and full of flavor. The addition of pancetta and black pepper added depth to the dish, making it a standout dish on the menu. For dessert, the tiramisu was a must-try. The creamy, coffee-flavored custard was balanced perfectly with the rich cocoa flavor and the light, airy layers of ladyfingers. It was a perfect ending to an amazing meal. One thing that really impressed me about Marsigliano's was their commitment to using sustainable and eco-friendly practices.They use only biodegradable containers and utensils, and they source their ingredients from local and organic suppliers whenever possible. This focus on sustainability not only benefits the environment, but it also adds a level of quality to the food that is hard to beat. In conclusion, Marsigliano's Pizzeria & More is a must-visit destination for anyone visiting Las Vegas who loves delicious food. Their authentic Italian flavors, attention to detail, and commitment to sustainability make this place a true standout in the city's dining scene. Whether you're looking for the best pizza in town or a delicious Italian meal, Marsigliano's is the place to be. So, the next time you're in Las Vegas, make sure to stop by Marsigliano's and taste the magic for yourself. You won't be disappointed!

name: Bettina
address: 1014 Coast Village Rd, Santa Barbara, CA 93108, USA
description_short: Denis Miller on the show! "Bettina: A Hidden Gem in Santa Barbara's Food Scene", Santa Barbara, CA is known for its breathtaking scenery and delicious dining options, and one restaurant that has recently caught my attention is Bettina. Located in the heart of the city, this hidden gem offers an unforgettable dining experience. From the moment you step inside, the warm and inviting ambiance will make you feel right at home.The decor is beautifully designed with comfortable seating, rustic wood accents, and charming lighting, all of which create a cozy and intimate atmosphere. But let's get to the most important part, the food. Bettina's menu features an array of dishes that are carefully crafted using only the freshest, locally sourced ingredients. Each dish is beautifully presented and bursting with flavor. The menu changes seasonally, ensuring that customers always have a new and exciting dining experience. One dish that I simply can't resist is the Grilled Octopus with lemon vinaigrette, potatoes, and grilled bread. The octopus is cooked to perfection, and the lemon vinaigrette adds a tangy kick to the dish.The grilled bread is the perfect accompaniment, making this a must-try for any seafood lover. Another dish that I highly recommend is the Roasted Chicken with root vegetables and pan jus. The chicken is juicy and flavorful, and the root vegetables are cooked to perfection. The pan jus adds a delicious depth of flavor to the dish, making it a real crowd-pleaser. For dessert, the seasonal fruit tart with almond cream is a perfect way to end the meal. The flaky crust, sweet fruit, and rich almond cream all work together to create a harmonious and satisfying dessert. Overall, Bettina is a must-visit restaurant for any food lover in Santa Barbara.The delicious food, warm atmosphere, and exceptional service make this place a true hidden gem. Don't miss out on the opportunity to try this fantastic restaurant for yourself.

name: Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe
address: 6110 W Flamingo Rd, Las Vegas, NV 89103, USA
description_short: Exploring the Flavors of the Mediterranean at Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe in Las Vegas Las Vegas is known for its glitz and glamour, but it's also a great destination for foodies. One of the best places to experience the flavors of the Mediterranean is Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe, located in the heart of the city. This small, family-owned restaurant serves up some of the best Mediterranean cuisine in Las Vegas, and it's definitely worth a visit. The first thing you'll notice about Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe is its cozy and inviting atmosphere.The decor is simple and rustic, with a mix of Mediterranean and Middle Eastern elements. The atmosphere is perfect for a casual meal with friends or family, and it's easy to feel right at home here. The menu at Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe features a variety of classic Mediterranean dishes, including falafel, shawarma, and kebabs. The flavors are bold and authentic, and the portions are generous. The falafel is crispy and flavorful, made with chickpeas, parsley, and various spices.The shawarma is juicy and full of flavor, with a combination of marinated meats, topped with a variety of toppings and sauces. The restaurant also serves a variety of vegetarian and vegan options. One of the things that sets Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe apart from other restaurants in Las Vegas is its commitment to using high-quality, fresh ingredients. The restaurant prides itself on using local, organic produce, and meats, which ensures that the food is delicious and healthy. The service is also great, the staff is friendly and attentive, and they're more than happy to make recommendations or answer any questions you might have about the menu.They are happy to accommodate any dietary restrictions. Overall, Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe is a great choice for anyone looking to experience the flavors of the Mediterranean in Las Vegas. Whether you're a local or a tourist, this hidden gem is definitely worth checking out. With delicious food, a cozy atmosphere, and friendly service, it's the perfect spot to enjoy a casual meal while exploring the city. In conclusion, if you're looking for a delicious and authentic Mediterranean cuisine in Las Vegas, Chickpeas Mediterranean Cafe is definitely worth checking out. With its commitment to using high-quality, fresh ingredients and its friendly service, this hidden gem is a great place to enjoy a delicious and healthy meal.

address: 209 6th St, West Palm Beach, FL 33401, USA
description_short: The story of The Butcher Shop Beer Garden & Grill began with the purchase of an old-fashioned butcher shop in West Palm Beach, FL, named Charlie's, known for its timeless recipes and commitment to quality meats. Igor Niznik, then a recent transplant to South Florida from New York and of Eastern European descent, quickly took to the creative challenges and demands of operating the shop, infusing his own flavor into the gourmet market, while his eldest son, Fred, was still living in New York, working in the restaurant industry and frequenting beer gardens.

name: Sparky's Landing
description_short: If you're looking for a taste of fresh seafood and a laid-back atmosphere in the heart of the Florida Keys, then you won't want to miss out on Sparky's Landing in Marathon, FL. This local gem was recently featured on the hit TV show Triple D Nation with Guy Fieri in the summer of 2021, and it's easy to see why.
description_long: If you're looking for a taste of fresh seafood and a laid-back atmosphere in the heart of the Florida Keys, then you won't want to miss out on Sparky's Landing in Marathon, FL. This local gem was recently featured on the hit TV show Triple D Nation with Guy Fieri in the summer of 2021, and it's easy to see why.Located right on the water in Marathon, Sparky's Landing is a casual and inviting restaurant that specializes in fresh seafood dishes and tropical drinks. The menu features a variety of dishes that showcase the flavors of the Florida Keys in innovative and creative ways, from the "Conch Fritters" with key lime aioli to the "Island Style Shrimp and Grits" with chorizo and pineapple salsa.During my visit to Sparky's Landing, I couldn't resist trying the "Blackened Fish Tacos" with a side of "Island Style Fried Rice." The fish was perfectly cooked and seasoned, with a nice crispy char on the outside and tender flaky flesh on the inside. The tacos were topped with a tangy and refreshing slaw that balanced out the spicy heat of the blackened fish. The fried rice was a delicious blend of rice, vegetables, and tropical flavors that perfectly complemented the seafood.But what really sets Sparky's Landing apart is the friendly and welcoming atmosphere. The staff was incredibly knowledgeable and passionate about their food, and they went out of their way to make sure that every customer felt right at home. The restaurant also has a dog-friendly patio, so you can enjoy your meal with your furry friend by your side.In addition to the delicious food, Sparky's Landing also offers a variety of tropical cocktails and local beers that are perfect for sipping on a hot summer day. The "Key Lime Pie Martini" was a standout, with a perfect balance of tart and sweet flavors.In conclusion, if you're planning a trip to the Florida Keys, be sure to make a stop at Sparky's Landing in Marathon, FL. With their commitment to quality ingredients, creative flavor combinations, and friendly service, it's no wonder why this restaurant was featured on Triple D Nation with Guy Fieri.

name: Citizen Cider
description_short: By early summer of 2014 the company had grown to more than 20 full time employees. They broke ground on Phase II of the Pine Street facility in an adjacent warehouse they had planned on leasing in a couple of years if they needed more space. In the midst of the 2014 scale up in production, Citizen Cider was underway building out an additional 9000 square foot production space complete with a full mechanical system and 13, 3200 gallon tanks to ferment and age hard cider.

name: Granzella's Restaurant
description_short: If you're on a road trip through Northern California and looking for a classic diner experience with some serious history, then you won't want to miss out on Granzella's in Williams, CA. This local gem was recently featured on the hit TV show Triple D Nation with Guy Fieri, and it's easy to see why.
description_long: If you're on a road trip through Northern California and looking for a classic diner experience with some serious history, then you won't want to miss out on Granzella's in Williams, CA. This local gem was recently featured on the hit TV show Triple D Nation with Guy Fieri, and it's easy to see why.Founded in 1976, Granzella's is a family-owned and operated business that has been serving up delicious Italian-American cuisine for over 40 years. The menu features a variety of classic dishes, from spaghetti and meatballs to chicken parmesan to lasagna, all made from scratch with fresh, high-quality ingredients.During my visit to Granzella's, I couldn't resist trying the "Garlic Bread" with a side of "Minestrone Soup." The garlic bread was perfectly toasted with a generous amount of garlic butter and Parmesan cheese, while the minestrone soup was hearty and flavorful with plenty of fresh vegetables.But what really sets Granzella's apart is the friendly and welcoming atmosphere. The staff was incredibly knowledgeable and passionate about their food, and they went out of their way to make sure that every customer felt right at home. The restaurant also has a deli and gift shop, where you can purchase homemade Italian specialties, olive oils, and souvenirs.In addition to the delicious food and welcoming atmosphere, Granzella's has a rich history that is evident throughout the restaurant. The walls are adorned with photos and memorabilia from the early days of the business, giving customers a glimpse into the past.In conclusion, if you're on a road trip through Northern California, be sure to make a stop at Granzella's in Williams, CA. With their commitment to quality ingredients, classic dishes, and welcoming atmosphere, it's no wonder why this restaurant was featured on Triple D Nation with Guy Fieri.

name: Tacos Chiwas
address: 1923 E McDowell Rd, Phoenix, AZ 85006, USA
description_short: If you're looking for authentic Mexican food with a twist, Tacos Chiwas is the place to be. This family-owned restaurant in Phoenix, Arizona serves up Chihuahua style food that will tantalize your taste buds. From tacos and burritos to quesadillas and empanadas, Tacos Chiwas has it all. In this article, we'll explore what makes Tacos Chiwas unique and why you should consider paying them a visit.
description_long: If you're looking for authentic Mexican food with a twist, Tacos Chiwas is the place to be. This family-owned restaurant in Phoenix, Arizona serves up Chihuahua style food that will tantalize your taste buds. From tacos and burritos to quesadillas and empanadas, Tacos Chiwas has it all. In this article, we'll explore what makes Tacos Chiwas unique and why you should consider paying them a visit.Introduction to Tacos ChiwasTacos Chiwas was founded by Armando Hernandez and Nadia Holguin in 2016. They named the restaurant after their daughter, Chiwa, and set out to create a menu that was unique to their heritage. The food they serve is inspired by the state of Chihuahua, Mexico, which is known for its diverse cuisine. Tacos Chiwas has gained popularity in the Phoenix area for their fresh and authentic dishes.The Menu at Tacos ChiwasTacos Chiwas' menu is an explosion of flavors. Their signature dish is the birria taco, which is made with slow-cooked beef, cheese, and a side of consommé for dipping. Other popular items include the al pastor taco, made with marinated pork and pineapple, and the chile relleno burrito, which is a burrito stuffed with a battered and fried poblano pepper. All the ingredients used in the dishes are fresh and sourced from local farms, making it a healthy and wholesome meal option.The Atmosphere at Tacos ChiwasThe atmosphere at Tacos Chiwas is casual and relaxed. The restaurant is small and cozy, with a few tables and chairs for seating. The walls are adorned with colorful murals that showcase Mexican culture, and the staff is friendly and attentive. It's the perfect place to grab a quick bite with friends or family.Why Tacos Chiwas Stands OutTacos Chiwas stands out for several reasons. Firstly, their food is unique and authentic. They've managed to create a menu that showcases the diverse cuisine of Chihuahua, which is not commonly found in most Mexican restaurants. Secondly, the restaurant is family-owned and operated, which gives it a personal touch. The owners are always present, and they take pride in the quality of their food and service. Lastly, Tacos Chiwas is committed to using locally sourced ingredients, which not only supports local farmers but also ensures that the food is fresh and of high quality.

name: Milly's Empanada Factory
description_short: If you're looking for a delicious and authentic taste of Latin America in Miami, FL, you can't go wrong with Milly's Empanada Factory. This family-owned and operated restaurant specializes in empanadas, which are savory pastries filled with meat, cheese, vegetables, or anything you can imagine. Milly's Empanada Factory has over 30 varieties of empanadas, from the classic beef and cheese to the exotic alligator and guava. You can also customize your own empanada with your choice of dough, filling, and sauce.Milly's Empanada Factory was featured on the popular TV show Diners, Drive-ins and Dives, where host Guy Fieri sampled some of their signature empanadas, such as the Cuban, the Philly cheesesteak, and the pizza. He also tried their arepas, which are corn cakes stuffed with cheese, meat, or beans, and their cachapas, which are sweet corn pancakes with cheese and ham. Guy Fieri was impressed by the freshness and flavor of the food, and praised the owners, Milly and Luis, for their passion and dedication.If you want to experience Milly's Empanada Factory for yourself, you can visit them at 13911 SW 66th St, Miami, FL 33183, or order online through their website, www.millysempanadafactory.com. You can also follow them on Instagram, @millysempanadafactory, to see their latest creations and specials. Whether you're looking for a quick snack, a hearty meal, or a catering service, Milly's Empanada Factory will satisfy your cravings with their mouthwatering empanadas and more.

name: Zemam's
address: 119 E Speedway Blvd, Tucson, AZ 85705, USA
description_short: Zeman's: The First Ethiopian Restaurant in Tucson, AZEthiopian food is known for its use of spices, herbs, and sauces, as well as its unique way of eating. Instead of using utensils, diners use pieces of injera, a sourdough flatbread made from teff, a gluten-free grain, to scoop up the food. The food is served on a large platter, usually shared by a group of people, creating a communal and social atmosphere.Some of the dishes you can find at Zeman's include doro wat, a spicy chicken stew with boiled eggs, tibs, a stir-fried beef or lamb dish with onions and peppers, and shiro, a chickpea flour stew with garlic and ginger. You can also try some of the vegetarian and vegan options, such as misir wat, a red lentil stew with berbere, a spice blend, gomen, a collard greens dish with garlic and ginger, and atakilt wat, a cabbage, carrot, and potato dish with turmeric. All the dishes are served with injera, which you can also order separately.Zeman's is owned and operated by Zemenfes Haile, who moved to Tucson from Ethiopia in 2019. Haile, who goes by Zeman, said he wanted to share his culture and cuisine with the people of Tucson, and also provide a place for the Ethiopian community in the city to gather and enjoy their food. He said he learned how to cook from his mother, who taught him the traditional recipes and techniques of Ethiopian cooking.Zeman said he is happy with the response he has received from the customers, who have been curious and adventurous about trying his food. He said he hopes to expand his menu and his business in the future, and also to educate people about Ethiopia and its culture.

name: crushcraft Thai Eats
description_short: At CrushCraft Thai Eats in Dallas, Texas, you'll find an authentic taste of Thailand right in the heart of the city. This popular restaurant has recently gained national recognition for its delicious dishes, thanks in part to a feature on the hit TV show Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives. In this article, we'll explore what makes CrushCraft so special and why it's worth a visit.IntroductionWelcome to CrushCraft Thai Eats! In this article, we're going to dive into what makes this Dallas-based restaurant so unique. From its vibrant atmosphere to its mouthwatering cuisine, CrushCraft has earned a reputation as one of the best Thai restaurants in the area.The Story Behind CrushCraftCrushCraft was founded in 2014 by chef and owner Paul Singhapong. Born in Bangkok, Thailand, Singhapong moved to the United States at the age of 10. After years of working in the restaurant industry, he decided to open CrushCraft as a way to share his love of Thai cuisine with others.The MenuAt CrushCraft, you'll find a diverse menu of classic Thai dishes and unique creations. Start with the chicken satay skewers or the crispy tofu, then move on to the spicy basil stir fry or the pad thai. Don't miss the signature dish, CrushCraft Fried Chicken, which is marinated in a blend of Thai herbs and spices and served with a side of sticky rice.The AtmosphereStep inside CrushCraft and you'll feel like you've been transported to Thailand. The restaurant is decorated with vibrant colors, traditional artwork, and ornate wooden accents. The open kitchen allows guests to watch the chefs at work, while the cozy seating areas provide the perfect spot to enjoy a meal with friends and family.The TV ShowIn 2021, CrushCraft was featured on the popular Food Network show Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives. Host Guy Fieri was impressed by the restaurant's fresh ingredients and bold flavors, calling it "the real deal" when it comes to Thai cuisine. The episode showcased some of CrushCraft's most popular dishes and helped to spread the word about this hidden gem in Dallas.Catering and Private EventsIn addition to its dine-in service, CrushCraft also offers catering and private event options. Whether you're planning a corporate lunch or a family celebration, the team at CrushCraft can work with you to create a customized menu that meets your needs.Location and HoursCrushCraft is located at 2800 Routh St #150, Dallas, TX 75201, in the heart of the Uptown neighborhood. The restaurant is open seven days a week, with hours that vary by day. Be sure to check the website or call ahead to confirm the current hours of operation.FAQQ: Is CrushCraft suitable for vegetarians?A: Yes, CrushCraft offers a range of vegetarian and vegan options on its menu.Q: Can I make a reservation at CrushCraft?A: CrushCraft does not accept reservations, but the wait time is usually short.Q: Is there parking available at CrushCraft?A: Yes, CrushCraft has a small parking lot behind the restaurant, as well as street parking in the surrounding area.Q: Does CrushCraft offer delivery?A: Yes, CrushCraft offers delivery through third-party apps like GrubHub and UberEats.Q: What sets CrushCraft apart from other Thai restaurants in Dallas?A: CrushCraft is known for its commitment to using fresh, high-quality ingredients and traditional Thai cooking techniques. The menu is diverse and innovative, with options for both classic and adventurous

name: The Wild Thaiger Restaurant
address: 2631 North Central Avenue, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
description_short: The Wild Thaiger is a restaurant in Phoenix, Arizona that has been making waves in the local food scene. With its fusion of Thai and American cuisine, it has become a go-to spot for foodies looking for something unique and delicious.
description_long: The Wild Thaiger is a restaurant in Phoenix, Arizona that has been making waves in the local food scene. With its fusion of Thai and American cuisine, it has become a go-to spot for foodies looking for something unique and delicious.The Wild Thaiger's menu is a fusion of traditional Thai dishes and American favorites, with a focus on fresh, locally-sourced ingredients. Their dishes are bursting with flavor and color, making it a feast for the senses. The menu includes classics like Pad Thai and Tom Yum soup, as well as creative takes on American favorites like the Thai Burger and Thai BBQ Ribs.The Wild Thaiger has a warm and inviting atmosphere, with colorful decor that reflects the vibrant flavors of the food. The staff are friendly and knowledgeable, always happy to recommend dishes and answer any questions. The restaurant is family-owned and operated, and they take great pride in providing their customers with an authentic Thai dining experience.At the Wild Thaiger we bring the flavors of Thailand to you, from aromatic Thai basil to the fire eaters delight! Come experience the best Thai food made with fresh authentic ingredients in the most creative modern Thai cuisine in the valley. Enjoy your meal with a variety of ice cold beers, elegant wines or cocktails from our full bar. This is the season for outdoor dining on our protected patio or dine inside and see our chefs preparing your meal on the fire wok!The menu at The Wild Thaiger is extensive, with something for everyone. Start with an appetizer like the Thai Lettuce Wraps, filled with marinated chicken, water chestnuts, and mushrooms, or the Spicy Crab Rangoon, which adds a Thai twist to a classic American appetizer. For the main course, the Pad Kee Mao is a spicy and flavorful noodle dish that is sure to satisfy, while the Thai BBQ Ribs are a must-try for meat lovers. And for those looking for something a little different, the Thai Burger is a fusion masterpiece, topped with peanut sauce and crispy fried onions.In addition to the delicious food, The Wild Thaiger also offers a wide selection of craft beers and cocktails, making it a great spot for a night out with friends or a date night. And with its central location in Phoenix, it's easy to make it a part of your next day out exploring the city.If you're in the Phoenix area and looking for a restaurant that offers a unique fusion of Thai and American cuisine, The Wild Thaiger is definitely worth checking out. From the friendly staff to the delicious food, it's a dining experience that is sure to leave a lasting impression.

name: Barrio Cafe
description_short: I recently visited Phoenix, Arizona, and had the chance to try one of the best Mexican restaurants in the country: Barrio Cafe. This place was featured on the TV show Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives, and I can see why. The food is authentic, creative and delicious.Barrio Cafe is a beloved Mexican restaurant located in the historic district of Phoenix, Arizona. The restaurant has gained widespread popularity for its traditional and authentic Mexican cuisine, as well as its inviting atmosphere and excellent service.Barrio Cafe is located on 16th Street, just south of Thomas Road. It has a colorful and cozy atmosphere, with live music on some nights². The service is friendly and attentive, and the chef/owner Silvana Salcido Esparza is a James Beard Award-nominated culinary master.The menu offers a variety of dishes from different regions of Mexico, with an emphasis on fresh ingredients and complex flavors. Some of the highlights are:- The guacamole, which is made tableside with fresh avocadoes, tomatoes, onions, cilantro and pomegranate seeds.- The cochinita pibil, which is slow-roasted pork marinated in citrus juices and spices, wrapped in banana leaves and served with pickled red onions.- The chiles en nogada, which are roasted poblano peppers stuffed with chicken, apple, pear, dried apricot and pecans, topped with an almond cream sauce and garnished with cilantro, queso fresco and pomegranate seeds. This dish is chef Esparza's signature creation and represents the colors of the Mexican flag.I was blown away by the quality and taste of everything I tried at Barrio Cafe. It was a memorable dining experience that I would recommend to anyone who loves Mexican food or wants to try something new. If you're ever in Phoenix, don't miss this gem!Barrio Cafe's appearance on the popular TV show "Diners, Drive-ins and Dives" hosted by Guy Fieri has further boosted its reputation and popularity. The restaurant's unique flavors and dishes have been introduced to a wider audience, attracting even more diners to experience the culinary journey of Barrio Cafe.

description_short: Re-branded as "Oak on Camelback" so take a look at their menu before you go as I highly doubt it's the same as when Guy Fieri visited.Oak on Camelback is a unique restaurant located in Phoenix, Arizona. This establishment has been serving its customers since 1998, and over the years, it has become a local favorite. With a menu that features American cuisine with a Southwestern twist, Oak on Camelback offers an unforgettable dining experience.
description_long: Re-branded as "Oak on Camelback" so take a look at their menu before you go as I highly doubt it's the same as when Guy Fieri visited.Oak on Camelback is a unique restaurant located in Phoenix, Arizona. This establishment has been serving its customers since 1998, and over the years, it has become a local favorite. With a menu that features American cuisine with a Southwestern twist, Oak on Camelback offers an unforgettable dining experience.One of the things that sets Oak on Camelback apart is its beautiful location. The restaurant is situated on Camelback Road, one of the most scenic routes in Phoenix. Oak trees line the street, creating a natural canopy that provides shade during the day and a cozy atmosphere at night. The outdoor patio is the perfect place to enjoy a meal and soak up the ambiance.The interior of Oak on Camelback is just as charming as its exterior. The restaurant is decorated with warm, earthy tones and features wooden tables and chairs that add to the rustic feel. Large windows allow natural light to flood the space, creating an inviting and comfortable atmosphere.When it comes to the menu, Oak on Camelback offers a range of dishes that are sure to please everyone. Starters include options like crispy pork belly and deviled eggs, while entrees range from braised short ribs to grilled salmon. The restaurant is also known for its delicious burgers, which come with a side of crispy fries.One of the standout dishes at Oak on Camelback is the smoked pork chop. This hearty meal is served with mashed potatoes and glazed carrots, and it's sure to leave you feeling satisfied. For dessert, try the pecan pie or the chocolate cake. Both are made in-house and are the perfect way to end your meal.Oak on Camelback also has an impressive wine list, featuring both local and international options. The knowledgeable staff is happy to help you choose the perfect bottle to complement your meal.Overall, Oak on Camelback is a must-visit restaurant for anyone looking for a delicious meal in a charming atmosphere. Whether you're a local or just passing through Phoenix, be sure to add this restaurant to your list of places to try.

name: Big Wave Shrimp
description_short: Located in the heart of beautiful Hawaii, the Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck has been delighting locals and visitors alike for several years. This hidden gem has garnered well-deserved attention after being featured on the popular food show "Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives," hosted by the enthusiastic Guy Fieri. With its delectable shrimp dishes and laid-back island vibes, Big Wave Shrimp has become a must-visit destination for food enthusiasts seeking an authentic taste of Hawaii.
description_long: Located in the heart of beautiful Hawaii, the Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck has been delighting locals and visitors alike for several years. This hidden gem has garnered well-deserved attention after being featured on the popular food show "Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives," hosted by the enthusiastic Guy Fieri. With its delectable shrimp dishes and laid-back island vibes, Big Wave Shrimp has become a must-visit destination for food enthusiasts seeking an authentic taste of Hawaii.Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck is nestled in a picturesque location, capturing the essence of the Hawaiian spirit. The tantalizing aroma of fresh seafood and the sound of crashing waves create an immersive dining experience. The truck's vibrant colors and friendly staff contribute to the welcoming atmosphere, making every visit a memorable one.The star of the show at Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck is undoubtedly their mouthwatering shrimp dishes. Whether you prefer them grilled, sautéed, or deep-fried, you'll find a preparation that suits your taste buds. Each dish is crafted with love and precision, using locally sourced shrimp that's renowned for its freshness and flavor.For those seeking a classic Hawaiian twist, the garlic butter shrimp is a must-try. The succulent shrimp are sautéed in a fragrant garlic butter sauce, resulting in a heavenly combination of flavors. Served with a side of steamed rice and a tangy salad, it's a simple yet satisfying meal that showcases the essence of Hawaiian cuisine.If you're in the mood for something with a little kick, the spicy chili shrimp is sure to please. These plump shrimp are tossed in a fiery chili sauce that will awaken your taste buds. The spice is perfectly balanced, allowing the natural sweetness of the shrimp to shine through. Be prepared to savor each bite and reach for a refreshing drink to cool down the heat.For those who prefer a crispy and satisfying meal, the coconut shrimp is a standout option. The shrimp are coated in a light, crispy batter infused with shredded coconut, giving them a delightful crunch. Served with a zesty dipping sauce, this dish combines the tropical flavors of Hawaii with a delightful texture.Beyond the delectable shrimp dishes, the Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck is a testament to the aloha spirit that embodies Hawaii. The friendly staff, always ready with a warm smile and helpful recommendations, create a welcoming environment that makes you feel like part of the ohana (family). The laid-back atmosphere encourages visitors to sit back, relax, and enjoy the beauty of the surrounding scenery while indulging in their delicious shrimp creations.Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck in Hawaii is a beloved foodie destination that has gained recognition far and wide, thanks to its feature on "Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives." With its flavorful shrimp dishes, breathtaking location, and authentic Hawaiian hospitality, it encapsulates the essence of the island. Whether you're a local looking for a quick and satisfying meal or a visitor seeking a true taste of Hawaii, Big Wave Shrimp Food Truck is a culinary experience that should not be missed. So, grab your appetite, head to the truck, and immerse yourself in the flavors of this unforgettable Hawaiian gem!

HRD Coffee Shop
description_short: A Dose of Flavor and Fun at HRD Coffee Shop if you're looking for a unique, flavorful, and laid-back dining experience in San Francisco, look no further than the HRD Coffee Shop. This hidden gem, located in the heart of the city, gained widespread recognition after being featured on the popular TV show "Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives."
description_long: A Dose of Flavor and Fun at HRD Coffee Shop if you're looking for a unique, flavorful, and laid-back dining experience in San Francisco, look no further than the HRD Coffee Shop. This hidden gem, located in the heart of the city, gained widespread recognition after being featured on the popular TV show "Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives."From the moment you walk through the door, the vibrant atmosphere and colorful wall decor welcome you with open arms. This cozy eatery has a casual vibe, making it the perfect spot for both locals and tourists to unwind and enjoy delicious food.HRD Coffee Shop is renowned for its diverse menu that combines classic American diner fare with a modern twist, inspired by Asian and Mexican flavors. Their signature dishes include the tantalizing Mongolian Beef Cheesesteak, the bold and zesty Kimchi Burrito, and the mouthwatering Crispy Tofu Rice Bowl.The portions are generous, ensuring that you won't leave hungry, and the prices are wallet-friendly, making it an ideal choice for budget-conscious travelers. The friendly and attentive staff go out of their way to ensure your dining experience is memorable, often striking up conversations with patrons and sharing the story behind the eatery's unique dishes.While HRD Coffee Shop is a bustling spot during peak hours, the wait time is minimal, as the efficient kitchen staff works tirelessly to keep up with the demand. Seating is limited, so be prepared to cozy up with your fellow diners or consider taking your meal to-go and enjoying it at a nearby park.HRD Coffee Shop is a must-visit destination for any food lover exploring San Francisco. Its eclectic menu, lively atmosphere, and memorable dining experience make it a standout among the city's countless eateries. Be sure to add this iconic spot to your itinerary and discover for yourself why it has become a favorite among locals and travelers alike.

name: Giuseppe's
description_short: Giuseppe's Restaurant: A Hidden Gem in Phoenix, Arizona Featured on Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
description_long: Giuseppe's Restaurant: A Hidden Gem in Phoenix, Arizona Featured on Diners, Drive-Ins and DivesIf you are a fan of the hit TV show Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives, then you know that Guy Fieri is always on the lookout for amazing restaurants that serve up delicious and unique dishes. One such restaurant that caught his eye is Giuseppe's, located in the heart of Phoenix, Arizona.Giuseppe's is a hidden gem that has been serving up mouth-watering Italian-American cuisine since 1989. The restaurant is owned and operated by Giuseppe “Joe” Naccarelli, who has been in the restaurant industry for over 50 years. His passion for food is evident in every dish that he serves.The Menu: A Delightful Mix of Italian and American CuisineOne of the things that sets Giuseppe's apart from other Italian restaurants is the variety of dishes on the menu. The menu features classic Italian dishes such as spaghetti and meatballs, lasagna, and chicken Parmesan, as well as American favorites like burgers, sandwiches, and hot dogs.The signature dish at Giuseppe's is the "Fat Boy" sandwich. This sandwich is made with Italian sausage, beef, and homemade marinara sauce, and is served on a soft hoagie roll. It is a hearty and filling sandwich that is sure to satisfy any appetite.If you are in the mood for something a little lighter, Giuseppe's also offers a variety of salads, including the "Super Chef" salad. This salad is made with fresh greens, turkey, ham, cheese, and hard-boiled eggs, and is served with Giuseppe's homemade Italian dressing.No Italian meal is complete without dessert, and Giuseppe's has you covered in that department as well. The restaurant offers a variety of sweet treats, including cannoli, tiramisu, and homemade gelato.The Ambiance: A Cozy and Comfortable AtmosphereGiuseppe's has a warm and welcoming atmosphere that makes you feel right at home. The restaurant is decorated with Italian-themed decor, including a large mural of the Italian countryside. The dining room is cozy and intimate, with dim lighting and comfortable seating.The staff at Giuseppe's is friendly and attentive, making sure that every guest feels welcome and well taken care of. Whether you are a regular or a first-time visitor, you will be treated like family at Giuseppe's.Why You Should Visit Giuseppe'sIf you are looking for a restaurant that offers delicious food, a cozy atmosphere, and friendly service, then Giuseppe's is the place for you. With a menu that offers a mix of Italian and American cuisine, there is something for everyone at Giuseppe's.Whether you are in the mood for a classic Italian dish or an American favorite, Giuseppe's has got you covered. The restaurant's signature "Fat Boy" sandwich is a must-try, and the homemade gelato is the perfect way to end any meal.So the next time you are in Phoenix, Arizona, be sure to stop by Giuseppe's and experience the delicious food and warm hospitality that has made it a local favorite for over 30 years.
